Same problem on my win10, but with another cause: Missing the "Microsoft Visual C++ {version} Redistributable".
  I install the "Visual Studio Build Tool" and solve the problem.

  The reason is: thrift-{version}.exe is only a "prebuilt Thrift compiler", it depends on some libraries, see [here](https://thrift.apache.org/docs/install/windows.html).
  "Visual Studio Build Tool" can provide these libraries, download it from Microsoft website and install it as follows:
1. In tag workload, check "Desktop development ... C++", and "MSVC vxxx - VS20xx C++ x64/x86 Build Tool" in right side;
2. Install.

 Then, all is OK.
